00:41:45,881 --> 00:41:48,419
Women want to know.
People want to watch.

537
00:41:48,509 --> 00:41:51,960
- Jill, you're not
working for the networks.
- No, not yet.

538
00:41:52,054 --> 00:41:54,971
I am tired of you
ignoring your assignments.

539
00:41:55,057 --> 00:41:59,517
- I suggest you drop the 'tude.
- Bob, I'm not doing a story...

540
00:41:59,603 --> 00:42:01,430
on fake orgasms.

541
00:42:01,522 --> 00:42:04,558
I am the one who
decides what the viewers
want to see, not you.

542
00:42:04,650 --> 00:42:07,686
Oh.
Fine.
Let's make this simple.

543
00:42:07,778 --> 00:42:11,194
- Shape up, or you're gone.
- Yeah.

544
00:42:13,075 --> 00:42:15,363
Yeah.
[ Videotape Rewinding]

545
00:42:15,452 --> 00:42:17,361
Bullshit.

546
00:42:17,454 --> 00:42:19,577
[ Westlake ]
Television really is
going to hell.

547
00:42:21,291 --> 00:42:23,913
Who the hell are you?

548
00:42:24,002 --> 00:42:27,039
I saw your broadcast
on Robert G. Durant
and Rollo Latham.

549
00:42:27,130 --> 00:42:30,499
You're very good.
Yeah.
What do you want?.

550
00:42:30,592 --> 00:42:33,510
There was a murder
on the east side
a couple of nights ago.

551
00:42:33,595 --> 00:42:37,344
- A man named Dr. Brinkman
was beaten to death.
- It's a violent world.

552
00:42:37,432 --> 00:42:41,098
Would you be interested
if I told you I had reason to
believe Durant was involved?.

553
00:42:41,186 --> 00:42:44,353
I'd be interested
if you could prove
Durant's alive.

554
00:42:44,439 --> 00:42:46,515
Brinkman
had a finger missing.

555
00:42:46,608 --> 00:42:48,517
This is Durant's signature.

556
00:42:48,610 --> 00:42:51,481
He cuts fingers off his victims
with a cigar cutter.

557
00:42:51,572 --> 00:42:54,987
Just because
there's a finger missing
doesn't prove anything.

558
00:42:55,075 --> 00:42:58,361
The killer
could be a lunatic
with a finger fetish.

559
00:42:58,453 --> 00:43:00,363
No. I don't think so.
Mmm?.

560
00:43:00,455 --> 00:43:04,370
Brinkman's building was
purchased by a company called
Inter-City Land Development.

561
00:43:04,459 --> 00:43:06,867
I'd like you to find out
who owns it.

562
00:43:06,962 --> 00:43:10,212
- How do I get
in touch with you?.
- I'll contact you.

563
00:43:14,052 --> 00:43:16,508
You'd better not be
wasting my time.

564
00:43:19,933 --> 00:43:21,842
Brinkman.

565
00:43:29,484 --> 00:43:31,394
Mr. Durant.

566
00:43:31,486 --> 00:43:34,690
Mr. Perkins.
Thank you for coming.

567
00:43:34,781 --> 00:43:37,699
It's an unusual pleasure
to meet an American
like yourself.

568
00:43:37,784 --> 00:43:40,536
Uh-huh. Let me tell you
something, Durant.

569
00:43:40,621 --> 00:43:42,779
This country
is going to hell.

570
00:43:42,873 --> 00:43:46,408
The police don't have
the weapons to stop it,
the courts don't have the will,

571
00:43:46,502 --> 00:43:48,411
and the people--

572
00:43:48,504 --> 00:43:50,876
Damn, Durant,
the people are bereft...

573
00:43:50,964 --> 00:43:54,748
of the fundamental guts
necessary to take back
our streets.
Precisely.

574
00:43:54,843 --> 00:43:57,963
And what is needed to
take back those streets
is firepower.

575
00:43:58,055 --> 00:44:00,676
New weapons
for a new age.

576
00:44:00,766 --> 00:44:03,886
This is the prototype of
a gun we like to call
"The Vigilante."

577
00:44:05,229 --> 00:44:07,138
In one fell swoop,

578
00:44:07,231 --> 00:44:11,774
this weapon makes obsolete
the guns of every criminal
in this city.

579
00:44:11,860 --> 00:44:15,775
You know, Durant,
I don't much like
science fiction.

580
00:44:15,864 --> 00:44:19,447
This isn't science fiction,
Mr. Perkins!

581
00:44:19,535 --> 00:44:22,286
This, sir,
is science "fact"-ion.

582
00:44:22,371 --> 00:44:24,743
This rifle
is a prototype.

583
00:44:24,831 --> 00:44:28,283
The production model will
be powered by plutonium
carbide batteries.

584
00:44:28,377 --> 00:44:30,998
Well, now.

585
00:44:31,088 --> 00:44:35,251
Uh, just what is the range
on this here thing, huh?.

586
00:44:35,342 --> 00:44:40,170
Oh, it will track and
disintegrate moving targets
up to three kilometers.

587
00:44:40,264 --> 00:44:44,012
Its range against
stationary objects
is limited only...

588
00:44:44,101 --> 00:44:46,806
by the...
curvature of the Earth.

589
00:44:46,895 --> 00:44:49,054
Shit. With this gun,

590
00:44:49,147 --> 00:44:51,639
we could save this nation
from itself.

591
00:44:51,733 --> 00:44:54,900
This is not recommended
for indoor use.

592
00:44:54,987 --> 00:44:59,696
Just what is the price tag
on one of these puppies,
Durant?.

593
00:44:59,783 --> 00:45:01,610
They are five
million dollars each.

594
00:45:01,702 --> 00:45:03,611
Batteries not included.

595
00:45:03,704 --> 00:45:06,740
- The initial production run
will be 20 rifles.
- When can I have 'em?.

596
00:45:06,832 --> 00:45:09,074
End of the week.

597
00:45:09,168 --> 00:45:12,334
Outstanding. It's been
a pleasure doing business
with you, Durant.

598
00:45:12,421 --> 00:45:17,332
You know, I always say
a man who can 't love
his own country...

599
00:45:17,426 --> 00:45:19,383
can't love a damn thing.

600
00:45:19,469 --> 00:45:22,305
- [ Chuckles ]
- Thank you, Mr. Perkins.

601
00:45:22,389 --> 00:45:26,932
You are a patriot, sir.
I'm just a man following
my own beliefs.

602
00:45:27,019 --> 00:45:29,225
There you go.
[ Whitey]
Gentlemen.

603
00:45:36,069 --> 00:45:39,485
Robert, do you think
it's a good idea...

604
00:45:39,573 --> 00:45:42,490
to sell to someone
who wants to fight crime?.

605
00:45:42,576 --> 00:45:44,984
Hmm.
Marvelous, isn't it?.

606
00:45:45,078 --> 00:45:48,993
As soon as he gets his hands
on those guns, Mr. Perkins
and his neanderthal nazis...

607
00:45:49,082 --> 00:45:52,083
