criminal organization
in the city.

608
00:45:52,169 --> 00:45:55,787
- Where does that
leave us, boss?.
- Without competition, Edward.

609
00:45:55,881 --> 00:45:59,713
In his patriotic zeal,
Mr. Perkins will level
the playing field for us.

610
00:45:59,801 --> 00:46:02,637
Besides,
in a couple of weeks,
he'll be out of batteries.

611
00:46:02,721 --> 00:46:05,129
Then we can use
the second batch of rifles
to consolidate...

612
00:46:05,224 --> 00:46:08,842
our interests in drugs,
gambling, not to mention
sales to our friends abroad.

613
00:46:08,894 --> 00:46:11,266
The resurgent
Durant organization...

614
00:46:11,355 --> 00:46:13,264
will have a complete,
uncontested monopoly...

615
00:46:13,357 --> 00:46:15,764
over every
criminal enterprise
in this city.

616
00:46:15,859 --> 00:46:19,524
Robert, I have to hand it
to you. You're a genius.

617
00:46:20,572 --> 00:46:22,612
I've always thought so.

618
00:46:37,256 --> 00:46:40,173
[ Man ]
Laurie, if there's anything
we can do, please let us know.

619
00:46:40,259 --> 00:46:42,168
That's very kind.

620
00:46:42,261 --> 00:46:44,419
That was beautiful,
Father.

621
00:46:45,806 --> 00:46:47,715
Take care.
Okay.

622
00:46:47,808 --> 00:46:49,847
Laurie.
Thank you, Gene.

623
00:46:53,564 --> 00:46:55,971
Hi, Laurie.
Hi.

624
00:46:56,066 --> 00:46:58,391
I'm sorry
about your brother.

625
00:46:59,862 --> 00:47:01,735
Thank you.

626
00:47:03,115 --> 00:47:06,032
I want to apologize
for the other day.

627
00:47:06,118 --> 00:47:08,443
No, no. I understand.

628
00:47:16,503 --> 00:47:18,412
I'm all alone now.

629
00:47:24,678 --> 00:47:27,596
I wish I could make
some sense out of this.

630
00:47:27,681 --> 00:47:29,590
You know?.

631
00:47:29,683 --> 00:47:31,723
I'm sorry.

632
00:47:31,810 --> 00:47:33,933
Did you know my brother
very well?.

633
00:47:37,274 --> 00:47:39,183
I was beginning to,
yeah.

634
00:47:39,276 --> 00:47:41,150
[Eddie ]
Miss Brinkman?

635
00:47:48,118 --> 00:47:50,989
Good-bye, Peyton.
I want to thank you
for coming.

636
00:47:51,079 --> 00:47:53,452
Really.

637
00:47:53,540 --> 00:47:55,449
Good-bye.

638
00:48:00,881 --> 00:48:05,459
It was kind of you
to send a car.
It was
the least we could do.

639
00:48:05,552 --> 00:48:07,461
Um--
[ Clears Throat ]

640
00:48:07,554 --> 00:48:11,054
I hope you know that
we share in your loss.

641
00:48:11,141 --> 00:48:14,225
Thank you.
Your firm's been very kind.

642
00:48:14,311 --> 00:48:18,178
Then we'll be seeing you
at the signing?.
All right.

643
00:48:22,903 --> 00:48:24,812
Thank you.

644
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:29,490
I think she really
digs me, man.
[Shutter Clicks]

645
00:48:29,576 --> 00:48:32,613
You take a look
in the mirror lately?.
[ Click]

646
00:48:38,252 --> 00:48:40,161
She does.
[ Click]

647
00:48:47,928 --> 00:48:50,845
[Engine Starts]

648
00:48:50,931 --> 00:48:53,848
[Limousine Pulls Away]

649
00:49:15,539 --> 00:49:18,374
You're late.
Your directions stink.

650
00:49:20,586 --> 00:49:25,544
I found out who owns Inter-City
Land Development: the late
Rollo Latham was the C.E.O.

651
00:49:25,632 --> 00:49:28,966
The original articles
of incorporation were signed
by Robert G. Durant.

652
00:49:29,052 --> 00:49:30,962
I knew it.

653
00:49:31,054 --> 00:49:35,135
Durant wanted to buy
the Brinkman property.

654
00:49:35,225 --> 00:49:37,467
When David wouldn't sell,
he killed him.
Wait a minute.

655
00:49:37,561 --> 00:49:39,969
We don't know
who killed anybody.

656
00:49:40,063 --> 00:49:43,646
Just because Durant established
Inter-City Land Development
doesn't prove he's still alive.

657
00:49:43,734 --> 00:49:48,396
For all we know,
he could be water skiing
with Jimmy Hoffa in the Bahamas.

658
00:49:53,285 --> 00:49:56,820
Maybe Durant's involved,
maybe he isn't.

659
00:49:56,914 --> 00:50:00,746
But our working relationship
isn't going further until
I know who I'm dealing with.

660
00:50:00,834 --> 00:50:03,290
My name is not important.

661
00:50:03,378 --> 00:50:07,957
I protect my sources.
I'm sure you do,
Miss Randall.

662
00:50:08,050 --> 00:50:10,007
