What do you need her for
when you can play with me?.

673
00:52:08,837 --> 00:52:11,624
I don't think so.

674
00:52:11,715 --> 00:52:14,502
Oh.

675
00:52:14,593 --> 00:52:16,632
Sometimes I play rough.

676
00:52:19,056 --> 00:52:20,965
Oh, hmm.

677
00:52:23,519 --> 00:52:25,428
Hi.

678
00:52:34,613 --> 00:52:36,522
Laurie!

679
00:52:40,577 --> 00:52:44,492
What are you doing here?.
Is there someplace
we can talk?.

680
00:52:53,215 --> 00:52:57,758
What's this about, Peyton?.
Tell me about those men
with you at the funeral.

681
00:52:57,845 --> 00:53:01,925
They're from Inter-City Land
Development. They're buying
David's building from me.

682
00:53:02,015 --> 00:53:04,767
That whole corporation
is a front.

683
00:53:04,852 --> 00:53:08,434
- They work for a man
named Durant.
- Durant?.

684
00:53:08,522 --> 00:53:11,060
No, I don't know anyone
named Durant.

685
00:53:11,149 --> 00:53:16,392
I do. And I'm here
to tell you that Durant
had your brother killed.

686
00:53:16,488 --> 00:53:19,655
No, the police said
it was an act
of random violence.

687
00:53:19,741 --> 00:53:22,149
Laurie, Durant wanted
David's building.

688
00:53:22,244 --> 00:53:25,494
When David wouldn't
sell it to him,
Durant had him killed.

689
00:53:25,581 --> 00:53:29,413
Do you have any proof
of this?.

690
00:53:29,501 --> 00:53:34,080
These men have been very good
to me. They helped me
with David's funeral.

691
00:53:34,173 --> 00:53:38,799
- They're offering a million
dollars for the building.
- A million dollars?.

692
00:53:38,886 --> 00:53:44,093
Is that what this is about?.
They killed David!
They tortured him!

693
00:53:44,183 --> 00:53:49,094
- Laurie, is everything okay?.
- It's fine, Bubba. Thanks.

694
00:53:49,188 --> 00:53:51,097
Okay.

695
00:53:52,566 --> 00:53:56,564
Look, I mean,
I don't even know you.

696
00:53:56,653 --> 00:54:01,149
I loved my brother. When David
left me the building, he gave
me a way out of this life.

697
00:54:01,241 --> 00:54:05,619
I can go back to school.
I can make a difference
with myself because of David.

698
00:54:05,704 --> 00:54:10,033
-It's all he ever wanted for me.
-It's blood money, Laurie.

699
00:54:12,127 --> 00:54:16,540
Well, I'm sorry, Peyton,
I'm signing the papers tomorrow.

700
00:54:37,694 --> 00:54:41,229
Do you have any idea how many
post office boxes there are
in this town?.

701
00:54:41,323 --> 00:54:45,024
I had a cop friend of mine
run the fingerprints you left
at the restaurant.

702
00:54:45,118 --> 00:54:47,076
You don't have
any fingerprints.

703
00:54:48,914 --> 00:54:51,072
Do you... Dr. Westlake?.

704
00:54:51,166 --> 00:54:54,084
They buried a box
full of ashes,

705
00:54:54,169 --> 00:54:58,249
but Peyton Westlake
didn't die in that fire,
did he?

706
00:55:03,178 --> 00:55:07,591
- Most of him died.
- Not many people rise
from the dead.

707
00:55:09,309 --> 00:55:13,177
You're news.
Durant's news.
I'm a reporter.

